msgid "Adaptation"
msgstr "Adaptació"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:149
msgid ""
"In GitHub we will create a project `https://github.com/AjuntamentDeBarcelona/"
"NOM-DEL-PROJECTE` where the code will be published.  The City Council has an "
"organisation-level account in GitHub called `ajuntamentdebarcelona`, which "
"will be the repository owner."
msgstr ""
"Es crearà a GitHub un projecte `https://github.com/AjuntamentDeBarcelona/NOM-"
"DEL-PROJECTE` on es publicarà el codi. L’Ajuntament té creat dins de GitHub "
"un compte a nivell d”organització anomenat `ajuntamentdebarcelona`, que serà "
"el propietari owner del repositori."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:151
msgid ""
"This does not mean there cannot be replicas (mirrors) of the repository, or "
"parts of it, on other sites (GitHub spaces of other organisations or "
"developers, the websites of companies awarded public contracts, etc.)"
msgstr ""
"Això no vol dir que no puguin haver-hi rèpliques (miralls) del repositori o "
"parts del mateix en altres llocs (espais GitHub d’altres organitzacions, de "
"desenvolupadors particulars, la pàgina web de les empreses adjudicatàries de "
"contractes públics, etcètera)."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:154
msgid ""
"It is recommended that the name of the project in GitHub be written entirely "
"in lower case, with the words in it separated by hyphens.  For example: "
"https://github.com/AjuntamentdeBarcelona/decidim-barcelona."
msgstr ""
"El nom del projecte a GitHub es recomana que sigui tot en minúscules i amb "
"les paraules de què està format separades per guions. Per exemple: https://"
"github.com/AjuntamentdeBarcelona/decidim-barcelona."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:156
msgid ""
"This is where the code has to be from the start of the project, without "
"waiting until there are any public releases."
msgstr ""
"El codi ha d’estar present en aquest lloc des de l’inici del projecte, sense "
"esperar a que hi hagi releases públiques."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:160
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Create a public repository on a different site to the City Council GitHub"
msgstr ""
"Crear un repositori públic en un lloc diferent del GitHub de l’Ajuntament"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:170
msgid ""
"There could be reasons that make it advisable to have the main repository "
"(the one linked to the issue manager) on sites such as:"
msgstr ""
"Pot haver-hi motius que facin recomanable tenir el repositori principal (el "
"vinculat al gestor d’incidències) en llocs com:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:172
msgid "The GitHub space of another organisation."
msgstr "L’espai GitHub d’una altra organització."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:174
msgid "Bitbucket or other similar platforms."
msgstr "BitBucket o d’altres plataformes similars."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:176
msgid ""
"A Gitlab portal of an organisation participating in developing the project "
"(or any future Barcelona City Council Gitlab portal)."
msgstr ""
"Un portal Gitlab d’alguna organització que participi en el desenvolupament "
"del projecte (o en un futur un portal Gitlab de l’Ajuntament de Barcelona)."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:178
msgid "Some of these reasons could be:"
msgstr "Alguns d’aquests motius poden ser:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:180
msgid ""
"It is a project many public sector participants intervene in and a "
"consortium or ad-hoc organisation is set up."
msgstr ""
"És un projecte on intervenen més participants del sector públic, i es crea "
"una consorci o organització ad-hoc."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:182
msgid ""
"The development company exercises strong leadership over the project, more "
"than the City Council might do, and wants the basic infrastructure under its "
"control."
msgstr ""
"L’empresa que desenvolupa té un fort lideratge sobre el projecte, més gran "
"que el que pugui tenir l’Ajuntament, i vol tenir la infraestructura bàsica "
"sota el seu control."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:184
msgid "In opting for this alternative, it must be borne in mind that:"
msgstr "Si s’opta per aquesta alternativa, s’ha de tenir en compte que:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:188
msgid ""
"We cannot give up Git as our version control system.  It is currently the "
"most widely used tool which all developers are familiar with and it offers "
"some good practices for open project management which would be much more "
"confusing with older systems (such as CSV or Subversion).  If certain "
"procedures have to be performed on another tool, for example, Subversion, "
"the solution is to do the development in open on Git, and keep a Subversion "
"mirror automated using the command `git ``svn`` ``dcommit`, as explained, "
"for example, at http://www.kerrybuckley.org/2009/10/06/maintaining-a-read-"
"only-svn-mirror-of-a-git-repository/."
msgstr ""
"No podem renunciar a Git com a sistema de control de versions: és l’eina "
"molt majoritàriament utilitzada avui en dia i que tots els desenvolupadors "
"coneixen, i facilita unes bones pràctiques de gestió de projectes en obert "
"que amb sistemes més antics (com CSV o Subversion) resulten molt més "
"farragoses. Si determinats procediments s’han d’executar necessàriament "
"sobre una altra eina, per exemple Subversion, la solució és fer el "
"desenvolupament en obert sobre Git, i mantenir un mirall Subversion "
"automatitzat utilitzant la comanda `git` `svn`` ``dcommit`, com s’explica "
"per exemple a http://www.kerrybuckley.org/2009/10/06/maintaining-a-read-only-"
"svn-mirror-of-a-git-repository/."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:190
msgid ""
"Either way, there has to be an up-to-date replica of the main repository in "
"the City Council GitHub space, to show all the contributions made to free "
"software projects."
msgstr ""
"En qualsevol cas hi ha d’haver una rèplica actualitzada del repositori "
"principal a l’espai GitHub de l’Ajuntament, per donar visibilitat a totes "
"les contribucions a projectes de codi obert que realitza."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:192
msgid ""
"The `README` file content (and markup) in the City Council GitHub space, the "
"GitHub.io space and the other sites with a source code link will indicate "
"which is (or are) the main repository (repositories) where development is "
"carried out."
msgstr ""
"Al fitxer `README` contingut (i mostrat) a l’espai GitHub de l’Ajuntament, a "
"l’espai GitHub.io i a la resta de llocs amb enllaç al codi font, d’indicarà "
"quin és el repositori (o repositoris) principal on es porta a terme el "
"desenvolupament."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:194
msgid ""
"Whichever they are, both the issue managing tool and the continuous "
"integration system must be public and capable of being used by everyone, "
"without paying subscriptions for any service."
msgstr ""
"Siguin on siguin, tant l’eina de gestió d’incidències com el sistema "
"d’integració continua han de ser públics i s’han de poder utilitzar per part "
"de tothom sense pagar subscripcions a cap servei."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:198
msgid ""
"All the project source code has to be downloadable by anyone at any time.  "
"GitHub makes that easy by providing buttons for downloading a `zip` file or "
"showing the necessary commands for cloning the repository using Git.  If "
"GitHub is not used, the repository's public site must also provide both "
"these types of download (`zip` file or `tar.gz` and command `git clone`)."
msgstr ""
"Tot el codi font del projecte ha de ser descarregable per qualsevol persona "
"en tot moment. GitHub facilita això proveint de botons per descarregar un "
"arxiu zip o bé mostrant les comandes necessàries per clonar el repositori "
"utilitzant Git. Si No es fa servir GitHub s’ha d’aconseguir que el lloc "
"públic del repositori faciliti també aquestes dues modalitats de descàrrega "
"(arxiu `zip` o `tar.gz` i comanda `git clone`)."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:202
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Use the [.line-through]#GitHub# main repository web interface as the project "
"development website"
msgstr ""
"Utilitzar el respositori de [.line-through]#GitHub# com la web de "
"desenvolupament del projecte"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:212
msgid ""
"The website's home page will be a `README` file in the repository root "
"directory.  This file can be in plain text, Markdown or other brand "
"languages supported by GitHub and which the latter interprets and formats "
"when the page is visited."
msgstr ""
"La portada de la web serà un fitxer `README` a l’arrel del repositori. "
"Aquest fitxer pot estar en format text pla, Markdown, o d’altres llenguatges "
"de marques suportats per GitHub i que aquest interpreta i formata quan es "
"visita la pàgina."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:216
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Establish access permissions to the main repository adapted to each type of "
"participant"
msgstr ""
"Establir permisos al repositori principal adequats a cada tipus de "
"participant"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:225 modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:327
msgid "Document"
msgstr "Document"

#.   links outgoing: link:#S_518[_S_518_] link:#S_A3D[_S_A3D_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:230
msgid ""
"GitHub uses the concept of repository *owner*, which corresponds to an "
"account that the City Council has as an organisation "
"(`ajuntamentdebarcelona`).  The other permissions are outlined in the "
"submeasures."
msgstr ""
"GitHub té el concepte de propietari (owner) d’un repositori, que "
"correspondrà a un compte que l’Ajuntament té com a organització "
"(`ajuntamentdebarcelona`). La resta de permisos es detallen a les submesures."
""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:232
msgid ""
"Anyone working for IMI who has a personal account at GitHub and is part of "
"the organisation `ajuntamentdebarcelona` will have admin permissions."
msgstr ""
"Qualsevol treballador de l’IMI que tingui un compte personal a GitHub que "
"formi part de la organització `ajuntamentdebarcelona` tindrà permisos "
"d”administrador."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:234
msgid ""
"Repository *administrator* permissions can be given to IMI staff and, "
"optionally, to each person in an external organisation participating in the "
"development under contracts with IMI."
msgstr ""
"Es pot donar permisos d”*administrador* del repositori a persones de l’IMI, "
"opcionalment, una persona de cada entitat externa que participa en el "
"desenvolupament sota contractes amb l’IMI."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:236
msgid "Sub-measures:"
msgstr "Submesura:"

#.  S_518::
#.  [sidebar.submeasure, id="{sect}.{counter:measure:A}"]
#.  .Submeasure {sect}.{measure}: Give all development team members permission to write in the main repository
#.  --
#.  [.tags]
#.  * Integration
#.  * Adaptation
#.  * Plugin
#.  * NewProduct
#.  * Publication
#.  * Document
#.   links incoming: link:#M_B3F[_M_B3F_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:255
msgid ""
"Give all development team members permission to write in the main repository."
"  That includes in-house staff and subcontracted people.  Also make the "
"current list of _committers_ public in a file in the repository root "
"directory called `MAINTAINERS`.  It must contain the name and email address "
"of each person."
msgstr ""
"Donar permís d’escriptura al repositori principal a totes les persones de "
"l’equip de desenvolupament. Això inclou tant persones internes com "
"subcontractades. A més, fer pública la llista actual de _commiters_ en un "
"fitxer a l’arrel del repositori anomenat `MAINTAINERS`. Ha de contenir el "
"nom i adreça de correu electrònic de cada persona."

#.  S_A3D::
#.  [sidebar.submeasure, id="{sect}.{counter:measure:A}"]
#.  .Submeasure {sect}.{measure}: Give everyone permission to read the main repository
#.  --
#.  [.tags]
#.  * Integration
#.  * Adaptation
#.  * Plugin
#.  * NewProduct
#.  * Publication
#.  * Document
#.  links incoming: link:#M_B3F[_M_B3F_]
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:272
msgid ""
"Give everyone permission to read the main repository.  Everyone must be able "
"to read and clone the code."
msgstr "Donar permís de lectura del repositori principal a tothom"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:276
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Give trusted outside developers permission to write in the main repository"
msgstr ""
"Donar permís d’escriptura al repositori principal a desenvolupadors externs "
"confiables"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:285
msgid ""
"If someone has been making quality contributions to the project for a long "
"time, on a similar level to people hired by the City Council, they can be "
"rewarded with permission to write in the repository.  This runs a low risk "
"because version control means that everything is traceable and changes are "
"reversible."
msgstr ""
"Si una persona porta molt temps fent contribucions de qualitat al projecte, "
"a un nivell semblant que les persones contractades per l’Ajuntament, se la "
"pot premiar amb un permís per escriure al repositori. Es corre un risc baix "
"amb això, perquè el control de versions fa que tot sigui traçable i els "
"canvis revertibles."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:287
msgid ""
"However, to avoid any misunderstanding, it must be made clear to that person "
"what the governance rules will be and who has the last word when it comes to "
"accepting contributions."
msgstr ""
"Se li ha d’aclarir, per evitar mal entesos, quines seran les regles de "
"governança i qui seguirà tenint la darrera paraula a l’hora d’acceptar "
"contribucions."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:291
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Integrate external contributions into the main repository by means of Pull/"
"Merge Requests"
msgstr ""
"Integrar les contribucions externes al repositori principal mitjançant el "
"mecanisme de Pull Request"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:300
msgid ""
"As anyone can clone the main repository and modify their copy, we don’t need "
"to give write permissions to anyone who is not part of the main development "
"team.  Everyone who would like to integrate a series of changes in the "
"product must submit us a Pull Request in GitHub"
msgstr ""
"Com que qualsevol pot clonar el repositori principal i fer modificacions a "
"la seva còpia, no necessitem donar permisos d’escriptura a ningú que no "
"formi part de l’equip principal de desenvolupament. Tothom que vulgui acabar "
"integrant un conjunt de canvis al producte ens ha de fer un Pull Request a "
"GitHub."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:304
#, no-wrap
msgid "Upload translations from the README file to the main repository"
msgstr "Pujar traduccions del fitxer README al repositori principal"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:314
msgid ""
"If the project’s potential users are mainly local, it might be a good idea "
"to translate the contents of the `README` file or part of them.  That can be "
"done by putting new files in the root directory of the repository, with "
"names such as (assuming that the markup language used is Markdown, and "
"therefore the extension is `.md`): `README.ca.md` or `README.es.md`.  In "
"this case it is worth linking all the translations with each other at the "
"start of each file.  An example can be seen at https://github.com/tiimgreen/"
"github-cheat-sheet."
msgstr ""
"Si els potencials usuaris del projecte son principalment locals, pot ser "
"convenient traduir el contingut del fitxer `README` o part del mateix. Això "
"es pot fer posant nous fitxers a l’arrel del repositori, amb noms com "
"(suposant que el llenguatge de marques utilitzat sigui Markdown, i d’aquí "
"l’extensió `.md`): `README.ca.md` o `README.es.md`. En aquest cas convé "
"enllaçar totes aquestes traduccions entre elles, al principi de cada fitxer. "
"Un exemple es pot veure a https://github.com/tiimgreen/github-cheat-sheet."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:318
#, no-wrap
msgid "Specify a project contact person in the README file"
msgstr "Especificar al README una persona de contacte del projecte"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:329
msgid "Include an email address."
msgstr "Incloure una adreça de correu electrònic."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:333
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use English as the language for all development"
msgstr "Utilitzar l’anglès com a llengua per a tot el desenvolupament"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:342
msgid "The following must all be in English"
msgstr "Han d’estar obligatòriament en anglès:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:344
msgid "Comments that accompany the code itself."
msgstr "Els comentaris que acompanyen el propi codi"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:346
msgid "Any document referring to the product’s design and architecture."
msgstr "Qualsevol document referent al disseny i l’arquitectura del producte"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:348
msgid "All the comments on the commits in the repository."
msgstr "Tots els comentaris dels commit al repositori"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:350
msgid ""
"All the entries in the issue manager and the discussion threads that flow "
"from them."
msgstr ""
"Totes les entrades al gestor d’incidències i els fils de discussió que se’n "
"deriven"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:352
msgid "All the discussion threads that accompany each pull request."
msgstr ""
"Els fils de discussió que acompanyen cada petició d’aportació (pull request)"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:354
msgid "The `README` file of the main repository."
msgstr "El fitxer `README` del repositori principal"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:356
msgid "The `INSTALL` file."
msgstr "El fitxer `INSTALL`"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:358
msgid "The `CONTRIBUTING` file."
msgstr "El fitxer `CONTRIBUTING`"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:360
msgid "The `CONTRIBUTORS` file."
msgstr "El fitxer `CONTRIBUTORS`"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:362
msgid "The `LICENSE` file."
msgstr "El fitxer `LICENSE`"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:364
msgid ""
"If the issue manager lets anyone enter issues and one is entered in another "
"language, someone in the team has to be responsible for getting it "
"translated or asking the author to translate it."
msgstr ""
"En el cas del gestor d’incidències, si aquest deixa introduir-les a "
"qualsevol persona i se n’introdueix alguna en una altra llengua, algú de "
"l’equip s’ha d’encarregar de traduir-la, o bé de sol·licitar a l’autor que "
"la tradueixi."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:368
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Do not upload to the repository binary files or files that result from build "
"(with exceptions)"
msgstr ""
"No pujar al repositori fitxers binaris ni fitxers producte del procés de "
"build (amb excepcions)"

#. type: delimited block *
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:380
msgid "Small images (icons, logos, etc.)"
msgstr "Petites imatges (logos generals del projecte, etc.)"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:385
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Keep the configuration information in separate files and in a different "
"private repository"
msgstr ""
"Mantenir la informació de configuració en fitxers separats i en un "
"repositori privat diferent"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:396
msgid ""
"This makes it easier to reuse the code.  It is incorrect to put the "
"configuration:"
msgstr ""
"Això facilita la reutilització del codi. És incorrecte posar la configuració:"
""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:398
msgid ""
"Hardwired in the code itself (see the ref:measure M_A69 <measure_M_A69>."
msgstr "Hardwired en el propi codi (veure la ref:mesura M_A69 <mesura_M_A69>."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:400
msgid ""
"In files where commits (changes) are made in the same repository as the code."
""
msgstr ""
"En fitxers dels que es fa commit (canvis) al mateix repositori que conté el "
"codi."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:404
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Do not upload sensitive information regarding users, the City Council or "
"third parties to the repository"
msgstr ""
"No pujar al repositori informació sensible d’usuaris, de l’Ajuntament o de "
"tercers"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:408 modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:519 modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:556 modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:573
msgid "Procurement"
msgstr "Contractar"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:415
msgid ""
"For example: configurations, usernames and passwords, public keys and other "
"real credentials used in the production system."
msgstr ""
"Com pugui ser: configuracions, usuaris i contrasenyes, claus públiques o "
"d’altres credencials reals usades en el sistema en producció."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:417
msgid ""
"Establish penalties (serious breach) in the contract performance conditions "
"for breaching this rule."
msgstr ""
"A les condicions d’execució del contracte, establir penalitzacions (falta "
"greu) si s’infringeix aquesta regla."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:421
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Re-synchronise own repository with the upstream project repository weekly"
msgstr ""
"Re-sincronitzar cada setmana el repositori propi amb el repositori del "
"projecte upstream"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:428
msgid ""
"[[repositori-de-codi-i-control-de-versions]]To finally enable our changes to "
"be integrated and our defect notifications to make sense."
msgstr ""
"[[repositori-de-codi-i-control-de-versions]]Per permetre finalment integrar "
"els nostres canvis, i que les nostres notificacions de defectes tinguin "
"sentit."

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:431
#, no-wrap
msgid "Issue manager"
msgstr "Gestor d’incidències"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:438
msgid ""
"One tool all free software projects need is an issue manager or bug tracker. "
" At the City Council we assign it the following functions:"
msgstr ""
"Una eina que tots els projectes de codi obert necessiten és un gestor "
"d’incidències. Als projectes de l’Ajuntament li assignarem les següents "
"funcions:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:443
msgid ""
"Provide notification of any defects detected (bugs tracked) by users and "
"developers.  Also to make their treatment, evolution and eventual solution "
"transparent.  It is important that the changes (commits) that solve a defect "
"(bug) point it out in their message.  https://help.github.com/articles/"
"closing-issues-using-keywords/[GitHub has keywords for this]."
msgstr ""
"Notificar els defectes detectats (bug tracker) per part tant d’usuaris com "
"de desenvolupadors. També fer-ne transparent el tractament, evolució i "
"eventual solució. És important que els commit que resolen un defecte o "
"assenyalin en el seu missatge. https://help.github.com/articles/closing-"
"issues-using-keywords/[GitHub té una sintaxi especial per fer això]."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:448
msgid ""
"Follow up tasks that are pending.  This enables one or more commits to then "
"be linked with the closing of an issue It is also possible to see who tasks "
"have been assigned to and how they are prioritised.  One option is to "
"specify estimated completion dates.  All this contributes to the "
"transparency and traceability of the development process."
msgstr ""
"Fer seguiment de les tasques pendents. Això permet després vincular un o més "
"commit amb el tancament d’una tasca. També poder veure a qui s’assignen les "
"tasques i com es prioritzen. Opcionalment s’hi poden especificar dates "
"estimades de realització. Tot plegat contribueix a la transparència i "
"traçabilitat del procés de desenvolupament."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:451
msgid ""
"Follow up how the contributions of the different parts are managed by means "
"of the pull request mechanism.  The bug tracker could even be open to "
"feature requests and the GitHub space could be used for publicly managing "
"and prioritising."
msgstr ""
"Fer seguiment de com es gestionen les contribucions de diferents parts, "
"mitjançant el mecanisme de pull request. Fins i tot es pot obrir el gestor "
"d’incidències a peticions de funcionalitats (feature request) i es pot "
"utilitzar l’espai de GitHub com a lloc on es prioritzen i gestionen de "
"manera pública."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:453
msgid ""
"It needs to be borne in mind that the bug tracker is not only important for "
"the everyday work of developers but also that many project observers use it "
"as a measure of how serious the project is."
msgstr ""
"S’ha de tenir en compte que el gestor d’incidències no és només important "
"per al dia a dia dels desenvolupadors, sinó que molts observadors del "
"projecte també el fan servir com a mesura de fins a quin punt estan davant "
"d’un projecte seriós."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:455
msgid ""
"This bug tracker has to be operational and public throughout the product’s "
"useful life, i.e. after the contracts with the City Council have finished."
msgstr ""
"Aquest gestor d’incidències ha d’estar operatiu i públic durant tota la vida "
"útil del producte, més enllà de la duració que tinguin els contractes amb "
"l’Ajuntament."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:459
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use GitHub/Gitlab for the issue manager of the project"
msgstr "Vincular el repositori principal al gestor d’incidències de GitHub"

#.  Once again it is the default option, in this case because of its automatic link with the GitHub repository and because it meets our accessibility and transparency requirements.
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:471
msgid ""
"Some basic issue categories will have to be established at the start that "
"can be modified later, depending on the needs of each project: `Bug`, "
"`Feature Request`, etc."
msgstr ""
"S’hauran d’establir des de l’inici algunes categories bàsiques d’incidència, "
"que després poden modificar-se segons les necessitats de cada projecte: "
"`Bug`, `Request`, etcètera."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:475
#, no-wrap
msgid "Link the main repository to a public issue manager"
msgstr "Vincular el repositori principal a un gestor d’incidències públic"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:485
msgid "If this alternative is adopted, it must be borne in mind that:"
msgstr "Si es fa servir aquesta alternativa, tenir en compte que:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:487
msgid "It has to be public, in the sense that:"
msgstr "Necessàriament ha de ser públic, en el sentit que:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:489
msgid ""
"Everybody has to be able to register as a system user without paying a "
"subscription, and thus take part in development."
msgstr ""
"Tothom ha de poder registrar-se com usuari del sistema sense pagar cap "
"subscripció, i així participar en el desenvolupament."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:491
msgid ""
"Everybody has to be able to see the issues and follow them, without having "
"to register as a user."
msgstr ""
"Tothom ha de poder visualitzar les incidències i fer-ne un seguiment, sense "
"necessitat de registrar-se com usuari."

#.  The GitHub issue manager meets both conditions.
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:495
msgid "It must be linked from the code repository `README` file."
msgstr "Ha d’estar enllaçat des del fitxer `README` del repositori de codi."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:497
msgid ""
"If the intention is for the issue manager to be part of the City Council’s "
"own infrastructure, it has to be one of the following free tools: Gitlab, "
"Redmine, Trac."
msgstr ""
"Si es vol tenir el gestor d’incidències en infraestructura pròpia de "
"l’Ajuntament, utilitzar una de les següents eines lliures: Gitlab, Redmine, "
"Trac."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:501
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use the issue manager for tasks, releases and new features"
msgstr ""
"Utilitzar el gestor d’incidències per tasques, entregues i noves "
"funcionalitats"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:511
msgid ""
"Integrating the repository with GitHub’s issue manager means that together "
"they make a good tool for collaborating on any code-related issue, not just "
"fixing bugs."
msgstr ""
"La integració entre el repositori i el issue tracker de GitHub fa que en "
"combinació siguin una bona eina per col·laborar en la realització de "
"qualsevol tasca relacionada amb el codi, i no només la resolució de bugs."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:515
#, no-wrap
msgid "Draw up and maintain an issue management policy"
msgstr "Redactar i mantenir una política de gestió d’incidències"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:524
msgid "It must specify:"
msgstr "Ha d’especificar:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:526
msgid "Issue type (defects, tasks, milestones, etc.)."
msgstr "Tipus d’incidència (deficiències, tasques, milestones, etc)."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:528
msgid "Stages for those that arise."
msgstr "Etapes per les que passen."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:531
msgid ""
"This task can be given to the company awarded the contract.  It it does not "
"have one of its own, IMI will have to provide it with one."
msgstr ""
"Se li pot encarregar aquesta tasca a l’adjudicatari. Si no en té una de "
"pròpia l’IMI n’hauria de proporcionar una per defecte."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:535
#, no-wrap
msgid "Give everyone permission to report issues, even anonymously"
msgstr ""
"Donar permisos per reportar incidències a tothom, fins i tot anònimament"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:546
msgid ""
"Configure the issue manager so it will not be necessary to create an account "
"to report defects or anything else, in order to facilitate as many "
"contributions as possible.  Activate the necessary anti-spam measures (e.g. "
"captchas)."
msgstr ""
"Configurar el gestor d’incidències per tal que no sigui imprescindible crear-"
"s’hi un compte per fer-hi reportar deficiències o qualsevol altre element, "
"per facilitar al màxim les aportacions. Activar les mesures anti-spam que "
"siguin necessàries (per exemple captchas)."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:548
msgid ""
"It is always possible to keep an eye on someone who gives us problems or "
"rethink this policy if it doesn't work on a project."
msgstr ""
"Sempre es pot vetar a alguna persona que doni problemes o reconsiderar "
"aquesta política si no funciona en un projecte."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:552
#, no-wrap
msgid "Put someone in charge of filtering issues as they arrive"
msgstr ""
"Establir una persona encarregada de filtrar les incidències a mida que "
"arriben"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:561
msgid "Someone needs to be given the job of deleting duplicates, spam, etc."
msgstr "S’ha d’encarregar d’eliminar duplicats, spam, etc."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:563
msgid ""
"Add a warning that it will first be necessary to look for duplicates and "
"check privately with another person that the problem reoccurs in a second "
"machine."
msgstr ""
"Complementar això amb un avís de que és necessari primer buscar duplicats i "
"comprovar amb una altra persona, en privat, que el problema es reprodueix en "
"una segona màquina."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:565
msgid ""
"Budget for this task if it is done under contract with a company or a "
"cooperative."
msgstr ""
"Pressupostar aquesta tasca si es fa sota un contracte amb una empresa o "
"cooperativa."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:569
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Notify the official bug tracker of the bugs in the product to be modified"
msgstr ""
"Fer la notificació de defectes al bug tracker oficial del producte a "
"modificar"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:578
msgid ""
"When we are adapting an existing product, one of the main contributions we "
"can make to the project is to detect, isolate and fix any bugs there might "
"be."
msgstr ""
"Quan estem adaptant un producte existent, una de les majors contribucions "
"que podem fer al projecte és ajudar a detectar, aïllar i solucionar "
"deficiències que pugui tenir."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:580
msgid ""
"Successful bidders should be contractually obliged to properly notify us of "
"the bugs, in accordance with the guidelines of each project, to help improve "
"the product upstream."
msgstr ""
"Cal obligar per contracte als adjudicataris a prendre’s la molèstia de "
"notificar correctament les deficiències, d’acord amb les directrius de cada "
"projecte, per ajudar a millorar el producte upstream."

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:583
#, no-wrap
msgid "Integration infrastructure and testing"
msgstr "Infraestructura d’integració i proves"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:590
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Link the main repository to a continuous integration system that run all the "
"tests, make the results public"
msgstr ""
"Vincular el repositori principal a un sistema d’integració contínua de codi "
"obert"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:601
msgid ""
"Use a free software tool that we can run in our own infrastructure if needed."
"  We recommend one of the following tools:"
msgstr "Recomanem una de les següents eines:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:603
msgid "Jenkins"
msgstr "Jenkins"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:604
msgid "Gitlab CI"
msgstr "Gitlab CI"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:605
msgid "Travis CI"
msgstr "Travis CI"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:608
#, no-wrap
msgid "Internal and external communication channels"
msgstr "Canals de comunicació interns i externs"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:616
msgid ""
"The first lines of communication between developers are the repository "
"commit messages and the issue manager threads.  Many technical decisions are "
"taken in these threads but the discussions that take place in them should "
"always be highly focused and strictly technical.  When the area under "
"discussion broadens out, it is necessary to resort to other channels."
msgstr ""
"Els primers canals de comunicació entre desenvolupadors son els missatges de "
"commit del repositori i els fils del gestor d’incidències. Moltes decisions "
"tècniques es prenen en aquests fils, però convé que les discussions que s’hi "
"duen a terme siguin sempre molt focalitzades i estrictament tècniques. Quan "
"l’àmbit de la discussió s’eixampla, cal recórrer a d’altres canals."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:619
msgid ""
"Initially all new projects have to create a development mail list or a "
"discussion forum, with public files.  This is the channel through which the "
"opinion of the different parties or individuals taking part in the project "
"is sought and strategic decisions are taken."
msgstr ""
"Tots els projectes nous han de crear inicialment una llista de correu o "
"fòrum de discussió per a desenvolupament, amb arxius públics. En aquest "
"canal és on es demana la opinió a les diferents parts o persones que "
"participen en el projecte, i on es prenen les decisions estratègiques."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:623
msgid ""
"At first there will not be much that separates the developers and first "
"users or early adopters as regards concerns and language, the latter usually "
"being highly motivated.  Consequently, in many cases the same channel will "
"suffice.  Later it may be necessary to create specialised communication "
"channels for different kinds of participants."
msgstr ""
"Inicialment hi haurà poca distància en quant a inquietuds i llenguatge entre "
"els desenvolupadors i els primers usuaris (early adopters), que acostumen a "
"estar molt motivats. Per això, en molts casos podran compartir el mateix "
"canal. Més endavant pot ser necessari crear canals de comunicació "
"especialitzats pels diferents tipus de participant."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:627
msgid ""
"Depending on the nature and make-up of the team, it might be useful to have "
"a chat room for more immediate communication.  Either way, it would "
"supplement the list or the forum, never replace it.  The list or forum is "
"where the whole history of the project (discussions, decisions, etc.) is "
"recorded for reference, a very valuable asset for the whole project "
"community, present and future."
msgstr ""
"Depenent de la naturalesa i composició de l’equip, pot resultar convenient "
"disposar també d’un xat que permeti una comunicació més immediata. De tota "
"manera el xat és complementari amb la llista o fòrum, mai l’ha de substituir."
" La llista o fòrum és on queda registrada de forma referenciable tota la "
"història del projecte (debats, decisions, etcètera), que és un actiu molt "
"valuós per a tota la comunitat present i futura del projecte."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:630
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Create a development list or forum that will initially do for users as well"
msgstr ""
"Crear una llista o fòrum de desenvolupament que inicialment servirà també "
"per usuaris"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:638
msgid ""
"Initially the project will have a single dedicated discussion forum, shared "
"by people carrying out development work and others who are just users of the "
"product, the early adopters."
msgstr ""
"nicialment el projecte tindrà un sol fòrum de discussió dedicat que "
"compartiran tant les persones que realitzen el desenvolupament com aquelles "
"que simplement siguin usuàries del producte (early adopters)."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:642
msgid ""
"We recommend using https://discourse.org/[Discourse], a tool that merges "
"traditional mail lists with a forum via web.  You need to activate the "
"options so anyone who so wishes can interact entirely be email.  A project "
"that uses this tool and which is undergoing trials at the City Council is "
"https://alvus.barcelona/[Alvus]."
msgstr ""
"Recomanem utilitzar l’eina https://discourse.org/[Discourse], que fusiona "
"les llistes de correu tradicionals amb un fòrum via web. Cal activar les "
"opcions per a que qui ho desitgi pugui fer tota la interacció a través de "
"correu electrònic. Un projecte que utilitza aquesta eina i que està en "
"proves a l’Ajuntament és https://alvus.barcelona/[Alvus]."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:645
msgid ""
"An alternative is to use Mailman 3.  The list could be called `NAME-OF-THE-"
"PROJECT-``dev`"
msgstr ""
"Alternativament podem utilitzar Mailman 3. La llista es pot dir `NOM-DEL-"
"PROJECTE-``dev`."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:647
msgid "Activate the file and use it profusely."
msgstr "Activar l’arxiu i utilitzar-lo profusament."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:650
msgid ""
"Initially in Catalan and/or Spanish.  When participants appear in other "
"languages, create a list in English."
msgstr ""
"Inicialment en català i/o castellà. Quan apareguin participants en altres "
"llengües, crear una llista en anglès."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:654
msgid ""
"The main developers must be present but they are not obligated to answer all "
"the requests.  Everyone participates on an individual basis in the list or "
"the forum.  If the people behind a product can be contacted, it engenders "
"confidence in the product."
msgstr ""
"Els principals desenvolupadors hi han de ser presents, però no tenen "
"obligació de respondre a totes les peticions. Al fòrum o llista cadascú hi "
"intervé a títol individual. Fa més confiable el producte que es pugui "
"contactar amb les persones que hi ha a darrera."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:658
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Create a mail list for people who use the product, if the project grows"
msgstr ""
"Crear una llista de correu per persones que usen el producte, si el projecte "
"creix"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:666
msgid "Activate the archive."
msgstr "Activar l’arxiu."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:670
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Create a development chat room for immediate communication between the team"
msgstr ""
" Crear un xat de desenvolupament per la comunicació immediata de l’equip"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/technical-infrastructure.adoc:678
msgid "Use https://gitter.im/[gitter.im] or https://riot.im/[riot.im]."
msgstr "Usar https://gitter.im/[gitter.im] o  https://riot.im/[riot.im]."
